      "comment": "HONG KONG PHOOEY (1) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, paving the way for a 0.8 lengths win at this track over 400m in 22.50. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Will go close again if runs up to latest. CHEERS JAX (2) was out of the placings latest but three back was a Free For All winner in quick time (16.00) at Cannington in a Free For All. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. MANX MAGIC (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 22.87 beating Sunset Vanadium. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. FLETCHER KEEPING (8) has strong claims after a long-odds top-three finish last time out.",
